============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/15-b8dddbe/feedback.md`. Summary of findings:

**Case 1 — KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA → `UuIw` (two bugs)**
- The book breadcrumb `/ Jesien / Zupy` (Autumn / Soups) at position 0 triggers the bilingual layout detector. Since it shares no words with `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` at position 1, the real title is falsely classified as a "translation candidate" and suppressed from scoring.
- After suppression, `UuIw` wins because its 4 letters escape the single-word garble filter (threshold is `<= 3`), and its 75% vowel ratio stays within bounds.

**Case 2 — LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS → `BALLS` (dedup destroys merged title)**
- The `capsCoalesced` logic correctly merges the 4-line title into `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS`.
- But `MAKES 25 LABANEH` (line 12) is filtered as metadata, leaving `BALLS` (line 13) as an orphaned standalone candidate. The "shorter wins" dedup then eliminates the correct title because `"balls"` is a substring of it with smaller length.

**Case 3 — Smażona zielona fasolka → `DLA & OSOB` (OCR corruption defeats metadata filter)**
- `DLA 4 OSÓB` (serving size) was OCR'd as `DLA & OSOB`. The metadata pattern `/^DLA\s+\d/i` requires a digit — `&` bypasses it.
- `DLA & OSOB` then receives the ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08). In the multi-title collapse, this bonus tips it above `Smażona zielona fasolka`, which earns no ALL_CAPS bonus.

**Common themes:** OCR corruption defeating hard filters; bilingual detection misfiring on non-title position-0 lines (` / ` breadcrumbs not filtered unlike ` | `); metadata fragments polluting the candidate pool; ALL_CAPS bonus overriding correct mixed-case titles.
